text.tspan: Unveiling Global Trends:
Socioeconomic Patterns Across Nations
*Last year available
Source: World development indicators. Washington, D.C. :The World Bank. url: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/
By: Paula Cadena
We often view other countries as vastly different from our own, yet closer
examination reveals a tapestry of shared experiences and common patterns. This
project delves into the interconnected dimensions of population growth, education,
and labor to uncover how these factors collectively shape the socio-economic
landscapes of nations worldwide. Leveraging data from the World Banks World
Development Indicators, this visualization series explores eight pivotal metrics
across diverse regions, each plot providing unique insights into the global
landscape.
Our journey begins with a global overview of population growth and migration
patterns, capturing movements between and within rural and urban areas. From
there, we investigate literacy rates and labor force dynamics, highlighting gender
differences in labor participation. Gender-focused analyses on wage employment
and youth engagement in education and the workforce shed light on regional
disparities and varied economic contexts. Finally, by comparing educational
attainment with GDP per capita, we reveal how education aligns with economic
development across time and regions. Together, these visualizations present a
cohesive narrative, illustrating how demographic trends, educational advancement,
and labor force engagement are deeply interconnected across borders, forming a
shared socio-economic fabric.
